      • getEndTime

        public final double getEndTime()
        Description copied from interface: Task
        Returns the end time of the task (exclusive). Should be equal to the begin time of the next task.

        This is a scheduled (planned) end time. To get a more precise estimate on the expected end time of the current task, use TaskTracker.predictEndTime(). The actual end time is a result of simulation.

        When the task ends, its end time (and the begin/end times of the following tasks) should be updated accordingly (see Task.setBeginTime(double) and Task.setEndTime(double)).
        Specified by:
        getEndTime in interface Task
